Citation.sTitle: Temperature dependence of the volumetric and acoustic behaviour of aqueous mixtures of monosaccharides and trilithium citrate
Citation.sAbstract: Densities (q) and speeds of sound (c) measurements of D( )-ribose and D(+)-xylose in (0.2, 0.4, 0.6) mol kg 1 aqueous solutions of trilithium citrate (TLC) have been carried out at different temperatures. The experimental results were used to calculate apparent molar and partial molar quantities, partial molar volumes and partial molar isentropic compression of transfer. The pair and triplet interaction coefficients are computed from transfer parameters. The partial molar expansibilities have also been calculated. The results have been interpreted in terms of prevailing interactions and structure making and breaking tendency of the solutes in aqueous solution of TLC.
